    http://blog.teamtreehouse.com/install-node-js-npm-mac

    USE brew install node
    Don't use sudo to install them as that will cause trouble later
    
    What's NPM?
    - a platform to share js codes - packages
    - It also makes it easier for 

2.) Go to Project Directory and run 

    npm init 

    which will create package.json
    It'll also ask a series of question

3.) Set permissions correctly 
    https://docs.npmjs.com/getting-started/fixing-npm-permissions
    so that you don't have to run sudo everytime

4.) Installing A Build System 

    Build System - Grunt, Gulp, Brunch
    What a build system do?
    - Reduce Repetitive Task
    - Prefixing CSS - autoprefixers
    - Utilities√è
        -JSHint
        -Uglify
    - Local Server 
    - Live Reload

    https://travismaynard.com/writing/getting-started-with-gulp

        npm install -g gulp
        gulp -v

    This one install a 5mb plus file call node_modules on local and updates package.json

        npm install --save-dev gulp

5.) Installed Autoprefixer

    npm install --save-dev gulp-autoprefixer

6.) create gulpfile.js

    touch gulpfile.js

